race.comment: ZOOMACHINO (7) improved again over a mile at Belmont and then went back and was narrowly beaten stepping up to a middle distance. Chris Parnham stays aboard and she's well placed to go one better. MISS GRAPHENE (6) comes out of the same race and was heavily bet to win. She didn't finish it off and the rider believed that she may not have appreciated the 7-day back-up. She's had three weeks away and deserves another chance. Pike goes aboard MIDNIGHT EXPRESS (3) and he's likely to show more over this distance. Has to be kept very safe. NEAP TIDE (2) is third up and suited stepping up in distance. Has ability and has place claims at least.
